<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1243> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1243" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Cic. Sen. 11; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Gurga [= Ruga ?] et Maximo Vero); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; and on Fabius, CIL 1\n     .1, p. 193- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.80; Tzetzes, on Lycophr. Alex. 603 (in Dio, LCL 2.41); see Degrassi 44f., 118, 440f. See 232, note 2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1222> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1222" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Albino et Rogo); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Zon. 8.18; and on Albinus, Liv. 23.24.3. See Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f. Albinus campaigned against the Ligurians (Zon. 8.18), while Carvilius served in Corsica and then, after the death of the Praetor, in Sardinia, and returned to celebrate a triumph (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 549; cf. Zon. 8.18). On Postumius, see Lübker no. 9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1221> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1221" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the cognomen Ruga, see Fast. Hyd. (Rogo), Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}), and Gell. 4.3.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10007> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10007" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Sardeis. MRR I.223-4, Itgenshorst no. 147, Rich no. 146." .
